defs.docs: A dead simple ANSI terminal color painting library.

defs.name: Paint
defs.docs: A structure encapsulating an item and styling.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Constructs a new `Paint` structure encapsulating `item` with no styling.

defs.name: masked
defs.docs: Constructs a new _masked_ `Paint` structure encapsulating `item`.

defs.name: rgb
defs.value: fn (r: u8, g: u8, b: u8, item: T) -> Paint<T>
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `Paint` structure encapsulating `item` with the
 foreground color set to the RGB color `r`, `g`, `b`.

defs.name: fixed
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `Paint` structure encapsulating `item` with the
 foreground color set to the fixed 256-bit color `color`.

defs.name: style
defs.docs: Retrieves the style currently set on `self`.

defs.name: with_style
defs.docs: Sets the style of `self` to `style`.

defs.name: mask
defs.docs: Masks `self`.

defs.name: fg
defs.docs: Sets the foreground to `color`.

defs.name: bg
defs.docs: Sets the background to `color`.

defs.name: disable
defs.docs: Disables coloring globally.

defs.name: enable
defs.docs:
Enables coloring globally. Coloring is enabled by default, so this
 method should only be called to _re_ enable coloring.

defs.name: is_enabled
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if coloring is enabled and `false` otherwise. Coloring is
 enabled by default but can be enabled and disabled on-the-fly with the
 [`Paint::enable()`] and [`Paint::disable()`] methods.

defs.name: enable_windows_ascii
defs.docs:
Enables ASCII terminal escape sequences on Windows consoles when
 possible. Returns `true` if escape sequence support was successfully
 enabled and `false` otherwise. On non-Windows targets, this method
 always returns `true`.

defs.name: Style
defs.docs: Represents a set of styling options.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Default, unstylized `Style`. This is identical to `Style::default()`.

defs.name: masked
defs.docs:
Default, unstylized but _masked_ `Style`. Aside from masking, this is
 identical to `Style::default()`.

defs.name: fg_color
defs.docs: Returns the foreground color of `self`.

defs.name: bg_color
defs.docs: Returns the foreground color of `self`.

defs.name: is_masked
defs.docs: Returns `true` if `self` is masked.

defs.name: fg
defs.docs: Sets the foreground to `color`.

defs.name: bg
defs.docs: Sets the background to `color`.

defs.name: mask
defs.docs: Sets `self` to be masked.

defs.name: paint
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `Paint` structure that encapsulates `item` with the
 style set to `self`.

defs.name: fmt_prefix
defs.docs: Writes the ANSI code prefix for the currently set styles.

defs.name: fmt_suffix
defs.docs: Writes the ANSI code suffix for the currently set styles.

defs.name: Unset
defs.docs: No color has been set. Nothing is changed when applied.

defs.name: Black
defs.docs: Black #0 (foreground code `30`, background code `40`).

defs.name: Red
defs.docs: Red: #1 (foreground code `31`, background code `41`).

defs.name: Green
defs.docs: Green: #2 (foreground code `32`, background code `42`).

defs.name: Yellow
defs.docs: Yellow: #3 (foreground code `33`, background code `43`).

defs.name: Blue
defs.docs: Blue: #4 (foreground code `34`, background code `44`).

defs.name: Purple
defs.docs: Purple: #5 (foreground code `35`, background code `45`).

defs.name: Cyan
defs.docs: Cyan: #6 (foreground code `36`, background code `46`).

defs.name: White
defs.docs: White: #7 (foreground code `37`, background code `47`).

defs.name: Fixed
defs.docs: A color number from 0 to 255, for use in 256-color terminals.

defs.name: RGB
defs.docs: A 24-bit RGB color, as specified by ISO-8613-3.

defs.name: Color
defs.value: Color::{Unset, Black, Red, Green, Yellow, Blue, Purple, Cyan, White, Fixed, RGB}
defs.docs: An enum representing an ANSI color code.

defs.name: paint
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `Paint` structure that encapsulates `item` with the
 foreground color set to the color `self`.

defs.name: style
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `Style` structure with the foreground color set to the
 color `self`.
